## Insecure External URL Handling

Two locations call shell.openExternal without validating URLs:

1. src/main/index.ts:35 (window open handler):
```typescript
mainWindow.webContents.setWindowOpenHandler((details) => {
  shell.openExternal(details.url)
  return { action: 'deny' }
})
```

2. src/main/ipc/systemIpc.ts:28 (notification click handler):
```typescript
if (openUrl) n.on('click', () => void shell.openExternal(openUrl))
```

## Risk
- Malicious renderer or compromised data source could trigger file:// URIs, leading to local file access
- Data:// URIs with embedded scripts
- Electron/node protocols in some versions
- If openUrl derives from unsanitized user input (e.g., API response), attacker controls navigation

## Recommendation
1. Whitelist protocol: only allow http:// and https://
2. Validate URL syntax (try URL constructor)
3. Add test cases for malformed/dangerous URLs

```typescript
function isSafeUrl(url: string): boolean {
  try {
    const parsed = new URL(url)
    return ['http:', 'https:'].includes(parsed.protocol)
  } catch {
    return false
  }
}
```

Apply before every shell.openExternal call.

## Evidence
src/main/index.ts:35, src/main/ipc/systemIpc.ts:28
